CoolConnect
Version 2.0 11/03/14

High Level Goals:
Create a chat client that works primarily using mesh networking
Complete basic meshnetwork + implement basic features + fix remaing bugs
Have all phones automatically connect to each other, and have the mesh networking completed

Sprint 1:
As a developer, I would like to know the code I'm working with (15)
As a developer I want a solid code base so I can expand on it effectively (31)
As a user I want a chat network to be as expansive and resilient as possible while
still being solely peer-to-peer so I can have robust interactions without relying on a centralized system (40)
As a user I want to chat with people nearby so I can have a simple and easy way of connecting quickly (6)

Sprint 2:
As a developer I want a solid code base so I can expand on it effectively (31)
As a user I want a chat network to be as expansive and resilient as possible while
still being solely peer-to-peer so I can have robust interactions without relying on a centralized system (45)
As a user I want to chat with people nearby so I can have a simple and easy way of connecting quickly (8)


Sprint 3:
 As a user, I want my phone to automatically connect to all other phones running CoolConnect so that I can join the mesh network. (32)
As a user I want a chat network to be as expansive and resilient as possible while
still being solely peer-to-peer so I can have robust interactions without relying on a centralized system. (36)


